$ PowerShell: formatting file

A *formatting file* is an → development/XML file with the → development/filename-extensions[extension] → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic/psHome/_format_ps1xml[`*.ps1xml`] that
contains the instructions for one (or more?) → Windows/PowerShell/language/object/console-display/views[views] that define how
→ Windows/PowerShell/language/object/console-display[objects are rendered on the console] by → Windows/PowerShell.

sa:
  In  → Windows/PowerShell/language/module/files/manifest[module manifest file], the formatting files to be imported when a
  → Windows/PowerShell/language/module is loaded are specified with the `FormatsToProcess` directive.

